      • onCreate

      • onResume

        public void onResume()
        Calls setDisplayedWeek() and displayEvents() to setup the activity upon resuming.

      • onPause

        protected void onPause()
        Removes all event buttons from the UI and clears the eventButtonList so that there will be no duplication of buttons upon this activity being brought back to the foreground.

      • setDisplayedWeek

        private void setDisplayedWeek()
        Updates the UI's week TextView to display the correct dates. It follows a format using SimpleDateFormat from java public libraries.

      • displayEvents

        private void displayEvents()
        Sets up and displays all of the event buttons for the displayed week. Fetches all the required events by using EventManager.getEvents(Date,Date) method and sets up the layout parameters for each event button using the global preferences (setupEventButtonFormat method) to retain consistent look and feel. Also calls methods inside this class to do the rest of the setup for the individual buttons.

      • getEventButtonParams

        private RelativeLayout.LayoutParams getEventButtonParams(com.example.calendar.Event event)
        Creates the appropriate layout parameters needed for the event's button to line up relatively to the hour markers on the left side of the screen and the day markers on the top.
        Parameters:
        event - the event for which this set of button layout parameters are being found for
        Returns:
        RelativeLayout.LayoutParams the layout parameters required for the event's button to line up with the axes of weekly UI

      • setupEventButtonListener

        Parameters:

        event - the event that this button listener and button is for

      • refreshDisplay

        private void refreshDisplay()
        Refreshes the UI to reflect any changes and performs necessary clean up. Removes all eventButtons from the UI and then deletes them from the eventButtonList to make way for future use.

      • todayButtonWeeklyOnClick

        public void previousWeekButtonOnClick(View view)

        view - the view that triggers this method upon being clicked
